
To install this script follow these steps:


1. Install the System Monitor Indicator package

    sudo add-apt-repository ppa:alexeftimie/ppa
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install indicator-sysmonitor


2. Copy the file smi-data.py somewhere in your pc


3. From terminal navigate to its folder and make it executable with

    chmod +x smi-data.py
    

4. Open the indicator-sysmonitor app typing it on a terminal or searching "System Monitor Indicator" in your dash.
   You will see something appears on your panel.
   

5. Right-click on it, then on Preferences, Advanced. Select the "Use this command" radio button and type the path of the smi-data.py file


6. You are done!
